    "faq_fFAwqm": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "text_XEPM9x": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is mad honey and where does it come from?",
            "answer": "<p>The honey harvested from high cliffs of Nepal which contains Grayanotoxin in it is popularly known as the <a href=\"https://medicinalmadhoney.com/\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Original Mad Honey \">Mad Honey.</a></p>"
          }
        },
        "text_bJtL4k": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is Mad Honey real or fake?",
            "answer": "<p>the hills of Nepal with its own special medicinal and psychoactive properties that benefit mind and body.</p>"
          }
        },
        "text_cU9Bya": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What are the effects of consuming mad honey?",
            "answer": "<p>Mad honey has a calming effect, reduces stress, and boosts energy, helping you feel revitalized. It also has mild psychedelic effects, enhancing mental clarity and creativity. Rich in vitamins and minerals, it provides you with a curl of energy and <a href=\"/pages/health-benefits-of-mad-honey\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"health benefits of mad honey\">improved health</a>.</p>"
          }
        },
        "text_B7TK9g": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is mad honey safe, and are there health benefits?",
            "answer": "<p>Mad honey is safe when consumed in moderation. It has a range of health benefits, including improving stamina, boosting immunity, and aiding digestion. However, excessive consumption can be unhealthy, so it must be consumed carefully.</p>"
          }
        },
        "text_UzHYFV": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How much mad honey can we safely consume?",
            "answer": "<p>You can safely consume around 1-2 teaspoons daily as a <a href=\"/pages/mad-honey-dose\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"mad honey dose\">safe dose</a>.  It’s recommended to start with small quantities and consult a doctor if needed. </p>"
          }
        },
        "text_6JXXi9": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How to Spot Genuine Mad Honey and Avoid Fakes?",
            "answer": "<p>Genuine mad honey is typically dark and has a bitter-sweet taste. It is harvested from specific regions in Turkey and Nepal. Always buy it from a trusted supplier, as copied or fake products may lack the desired effects.</p>"
          }
        },
        "text_3UNgd6": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Why is mad honey Hallucinogenic?",
            "answer": "<p>Mad honey contains a unique compound called grayanotoxin, which gives it mild hallucinogenic properties. This compound helps calm the mind and is often appreciated for its relaxing effects, making it a natural choice for those seeking relief from daily stress. </p>"
          }
        },
        "text_YjkEjC": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Why mad honey is better than regular honey?",
            "answer": "<p>Mad honey stands out from regular honey by offering more than just nutrients. It provides benefits like better mental clarity, creativity, and a calming effect that lacks in regular honey. With potent antioxidants, vitamins, and minerals, it boosts immunity, and energy making it a superior choice for natural health.</p>"
          }
        },
        "text_Gd6WJK": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long do the effects of mad honey last?",
            "answer": "<p>The effects of mad honey typically begin within 5-10 minutes and may last anywhere from an hour to several hours, depending on the amount consumed. Initially strong, the effects gradually fade over time in one day.</p>"
          }
        },
        "text_P9NyGb": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is mad honey legal?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes, <a href=\"/pages/is-mad-honey-legal\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"Is Mad Honey Legal?\">mad honey is legal</a> in most of the countries. In the U.S. and Canada, mad honey is allowed if it meets health guidelines. Nepal has specific rules for its production and labeling. Most European countries permit it if properly labeled, though some, like Spain, have additional restrictions.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
